                {{/if}}
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2>Ten Belles</h2>
                <h4>10 rue de la Grange-aux-Belles, 75010</h4>
                <p>First thing in the morning, I drink a Capuccino. Then, I move to plenty of espresso. I try to stop drinking coffee around 1pm so I can take a nap before the night shift begins.</p>
                {{#if session.user}}
                    <a class='add-restaurant' data-id='88'>Add to your list</a>
                {{else}}
                    <a href='#' class='login-modal'>Add to your list</a>
                {{/if}}
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2>Du pain et des idées</h2>
                <h4>34 Rue Yves Toudic, 75010</h4>
                <p>We get our bread here for the restaurant. When it’s my turn to pick up (as the baker won’t deliver the bread), i like to grab a chausson aux pommes or an escargot. They’re too good to be true.</p>
                {{#if session.user}}
                    <a class='add-restaurant' data-id='145'>Add to your list</a>
                {{else}}
                    <a href='#' class='login-modal'>Add to your list</a>
                {{/if}}
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2>L’Ambroisie</h2>
                <h4>9 Place des Vosges, 75004</h4>
                <p>It was a December 26th, and Marie and I were in front of Sacre-Coeur enjoying the incredible view of Paris. It was snowing heavily and we were practically alone, only a Japanese couple taking pictures in the distance. I knelt in the snow, and asked for her hand... Then we went to eat at L’Ambroisie, one of the best three Michelin starred restaurant in Paris !</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2>Marché Président Wilson, 16<sup>ème</sup></h2>
                <p>This market is well known for the vegetables of Joel Thiebault. I go there sometimes to get away from rue du Nil and soak up all of the fresh delights.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2>Lockwood</h2>
                <h4>73 rue d’Aboukir, 75002</h4>
                <p>I really like the Negroni and all of their bitter cocktails in general. Romain, the bartender at Lockwood, knows my tastes. Each time I go there, I’m his guinea pig, trying a new recipe. I love it !</p>
                {{#if session.user}}
                    <a class='add-restaurant' data-id='98'>Add to your list</a>
                {{else}}
                    <a href='#' class='login-modal'>Add to your list</a>
                {{/if}}
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2>L’Astrance</h2>
                <p>I normally go here once or twice a year. I love everything. The service is great. And also the food, of course!</p>
                {{#if session.user}}
                    <a class='add-restaurant' data-id='62'>Add to your list</a>
                {{else}}
                    <a href='#' class='login-modal'>Add to your list</a>
                {{/if}}
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2>Le Coq Rico</h2>
                <h4>98 Rue Lepic, 75018</h4>
                <p>Le Coq Rico, Marie and I love going here with the kids on Sunday to have a proper roast chicken.</p>
                {{#if session.user}}
                    <a class='add-restaurant' data-id='58'>Add to your list</a>
                {{else}}
                    <a href='#' class='login-modal'>Add to your list</a>
                {{/if}}
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2>Jardin des Tuileries</h2>
                <p>As long as the weather is good, we like to picnic in the Tuileries Garden with our friends. Everyone brings a little something. I usually bring a terrine from the fridge of the restaurant and always some good, cold beer in a cooler bag. My favorite? La Perle !</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2>Shopping in the 6<sup>ème</sup></h2>
                <p>Sometimes I disappear from the house and come back with tons of bags. which amuses my wife… Usually I make my way through the 6 ème  and the Marais. I like APC, Acne, Paul Smith and NDC for their shoes. Oh, and also Merci for their clothes and dishes!</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2>Encore</h2>
                <h4>43 Rue Richer, 75009</h4>
                <p>The boss, Franck, is a good friend of mine. We tend to sit and the bar and chat while I’m eating. It’s even better now with their new chef.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2>Le cirque d’hiver</h2>
                <p>We brought the kids to le Cirque d’hiver. Everyone loved it !</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2>Le Dauphin</h2>
                <h4>131 Avenue Parmentier, 75011</h4>
                <p>I like this place because they cook exactly as I like to eat. A lot of little dishes like my wine bar. And I really like Franck (the head waiter).</p>
